---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="About - Your Name"
  description="About Your Name - background, interests, and current work"
>
  <Header />
  
  <main class="main-content">
    <div class="container">
      <article class="about-content">
        <h1 class="page-title">about</h1>
        
        <div class="content-body">
          <p>I'm a designer and programmer interested in the intersection of computing, cognition, and creativity. I spend my time building tools and interfaces that augment human thinking rather than merely automate tasks.</p>
          
          <p>Much of my work is inspired by researchers like <a href="https://andymatuschak.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Andy Matuschak</a>, <a href="https://worrydream.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bret Victor</a>, and <a href="https://numinous.productions/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Michael Nielsen</a>, who explore how we can use technology to make abstract ideas more concrete and manipulable.</p>
          
          <h2>current work</h2>
          <p>I'm currently working on tools for reading, writing, and thinking—software that helps people engage more deeply with complex ideas. This includes:</p>
          
          <ul>
            <li>Interactive reading environments that make it easier to annotate, link, and remember what you read</li>
            <li>Dynamic documents that blend text with live computation and visualization</li>
            <li>Interfaces for exploring and organizing knowledge</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2>background</h2>
          <p>I studied computer science and cognitive science, with a focus on human-computer interaction. I've worked as both a software engineer and a product designer, always gravitating toward projects that involve making complex systems more understandable and usable.</p>
          
          <p>I believe that the most interesting problems in technology aren't purely technical—they're about understanding how people think, learn, and create, and then building tools that support and extend those natural processes.</p>
          
          <h2>influences</h2>
          <p>Some people and ideas that have shaped my thinking:</p>
          
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Douglas Engelbart</strong> on augmenting human intellect through computing</li>
            <li><strong>Seymour Papert</strong> on learning through making and the power of constructive environments</li>
            <li><strong>Donald Norman</strong> on the design of everyday things and the psychology of interaction</li>
            <li><strong>Vannevar Bush</strong> on associative thinking and the memex</li>
            <li><strong>Ted Nelson</strong> on hypertext and literary machines</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2>philosophy</h2>
          <p>I believe software should be:</p>
          
          <ul>
            <li><strong>explorable</strong> — encouraging experimentation and discovery</li>
            <li><strong>transparent</strong> — making its behavior understandable and predictable</li>
            <li><strong>empowering</strong> — giving people agency over their tools and data</li>
            <li><strong>beautiful</strong> — delightful to use and aesthetically pleasing</li>
          </ul>
          
          <p>Most importantly, I think we should design technology that makes us more human, not less—tools that enhance our natural capabilities for curiosity, creativity, and connection.</p>
          
          <h2>contact</h2>
          <p>I'm always interested in connecting with people working on similar ideas. Feel free to reach out:</p>
          
          <ul class="contact-list">
            <li>email: <a href="mailto:your.email@example.com">your.email@example.com</a></li>
            <li>twitter: <a href="https://twitter.com/yourusername" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@yourusername</a></li>
            <li>github: <a href="https://github.com/yourusername" target="_blank" rel="noopener">yourusername</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .main-content {
    flex: 1;
  }
  
  .container {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-2xl) var(--space-lg);
  }
  
  .about-content {
    max-width: 100%;
  }
  
  .page-title {
    font-family: var(--font-family-mono);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-2xl);
    text-transform: lowercase;
  }
  
  .content-body {
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  
  .content-body p {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }
  
  .content-body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-family-mono);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: var(--space-2xl) 0 var(--space-lg);
    text-transform: lowercase;
  }
  
  .content-body ul {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-lg);
    padding-left: var(--space-xl);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }
  
  .content-body li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }
  
  .content-body a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  
  .content-body a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent-hover);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  
  .content-body strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  
  .contact-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding-left: 0;
  }
  
  .contact-list li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .container {
      padding: var(--space-xl) var(--space-md);
    }
  }
</style>